{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-ae159a8a5f8726f4","input":{"filename":"cloud_cost_action_report.md","title":"Prioritized Cloud Cost Optimization Actions","markdown":"# Prioritized Cloud Cost Optimization Actions (under 500 words)\n\n**Evidence Base**\n- Dossier loaded for Cloud Cost Optimizer (ID: 08-cloud-cost-optimizer).\n- Records analyzed (limit 20) yielded **3** relevant items with a combined risk score of **17** and opportunity score of **11.5**.\n- Top‑ranked record **08‑A** (impact $44,536, risk 5, opportunity 8.5) is marked *urgent*.\n- Secondary items **08‑C** (impact $19,688, risk 3, opportunity 2) is *blocked* pending cross‑functional input, and **08‑B** (impact $9,904, risk 3, opportunity 1) is *in review*.\n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ Immediate High‑Impact Action – Record 08‑A\n**Goal:** Capture the largest avoidable spend quickly with low risk.\n\n| Category | Typical Levers | Rationale |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Rightsizing** | Identify under‑utilized compute (e.g., EC2, GKE nodes) and shrink instance sizes or autoscaling thresholds. | The urgent record indicates a sizable $44k impact, suggesting a substantial over‑provisioned resource pool.\n| **Reservation / Savings Plans** | Convert steady‑state workloads to 1‑year or 3‑year Reserved Instances or Savings Plans. | Immediate commitment locks down current usage at a discount, reducing cost without architectural change.\n| **Deletion** | Spot and terminate idle resources (e.g., unattached EBS volumes, idle IPs, unused snapshots). | Quick wins with negligible risk; aligns with the “low‑risk” mandate.\n\n**Proposed Steps**\n1. Pull the latest utilization metrics for the top‑cost services (Compute Engine, Cloud SQL, etc.).\n2. Run a rightsizing script (e.g., AWS Compute Optimizer, GCP Recommender) to surface candidates.\n3. Validate candidates with owners (1‑day turnaround) and apply size reductions or terminate idle assets.\n4. For any consistently‑used workloads, generate a reservation plan covering at least 70% of usage.\n\n**Estimated Savings**: 20‑30% of the $44k impact → **$9k‑$13k / month**.\n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Secondary Action – Record 08‑C (Blocked)\n**Context:** Requires coordination before recommendation.\n- **Potential Levers:** Architecture‑level refactor (e.g., moving from on‑prem VPN to Cloud NAT) or consolidating redundant environments.\n- **Next Step:** Schedule a sync with the owning team to clarify constraints and define a low‑risk pilot.\n- **Assumption:** Once unblocked, similar rightsizing and reservation levers will apply, with an estimated 10‑15% saving (~$2k‑$3k / month).\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Review‑Stage Action – Record 08‑B\n**Goal:** Use this queue item as a validation baseline.\n- Apply the same rightsizing/deletion checklist used for 08‑A.\n- Document any differences in impact to refine the scoring model.\n- Expected modest savings (~$1k / month).\n\n---\n\n## Prioritization Summary\n| Priority | Record | Impact ($) | Recommended Lever(s) | Expected Savings |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **High** | 08‑A (Urgent) | 44,536 | Rightsizing, Deletion, Reservations | 9k‑13k/mo |\n| **Medium** | 08‑C (Blocked) | 19,688 | Architecture review, Reservations | 2k‑3k/mo |\n| **Low** | 08‑B (In Review) | 9,904 | Rightsizing, Deletion | ~1k/mo |\n\n---\n\n## Assumptions & Uncertainties\n- Utilization data is up‑to‑date; stale metrics could affect rightsizing accuracy.\n- Reservation discounts assume standard pricing; spot market fluctuations are not modeled.\n- Cross‑team dependencies for 08‑C may introduce schedule risk.\n\n---\n\n## Next Actions (Owner: Platform Cloud‑Cost Team)\n1. **Data Pull** – Retrieve latest usage metrics (within 1 day).\n2. **Stakeholder Review** – Share candidate rightsizing list with service owners (Day 2).\n3. **Apply Changes** – Execute deletions and size adjustments (Day 3‑5).\n4. **Reservation Planning** – Draft a 1‑yr Savings Plan for stable workloads (Day 5‑7).\n5. **Coordinate 08‑C** – Book a joint meeting to unblock the record (within 2 weeks).\n\n*All actions are low‑risk, reversible, and align with the Cloud Cost Optimizer’s mandate to capture avoidable spend.*\n"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:07:32.532Z"}}
